Daniel J. Brestle: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 22, 2017 7:26 PM ET
Capital Markets

Company Overview of GF Capital Management & Advisors, LLC



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Daniel J. Brestle  Senior Advisor, GF Capital Management & Advisors, LLCAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships71--
Background

		Mr. Daniel J. Brestle, also known as Dan, is a Senior Advisor at GF Capital Management & Advisors, LLC since 2009. Mr. Brestle served as a Vice Chairman and President of The Estee Lauder Companies Inc., until his retirement in June 2009 after spending more than 30 years in leadership positions within the Lauder organization and its family of brands. He served as the President of ELC NA for Estee Lauder Companies Inc. Mr. Brestle served as the Chief Operating Officer ... of Estee Lauder Companies Inc., since January 1, 2005 and its Group President of the Company's high growth specialty brands from July 2001 to January 2005. He began his career as a Distribution and Plant Manager at Estee Lauder. From July 1998 to June 2001, Mr. Brestle served as the President of Estee Lauder. Mr. Brestle joined Estee Lauder Companies Inc. in 1978. Mr. Brestle served as a Vice Chairman and Director of Estee Lauder Companies Inc. He was responsible for Global Operations and Research and Development and oversaw the Estée Lauder, Jo Malone, La Mer, MoAoC and Prescriptives brands and its BeautyBank division. Mr. Brestle was responsible for Aveda, Bobbi Brown, Bumble and bumble, La Mer, Prescriptives, jane, Jo Malone, Kate Spade and Stila on a worldwide basis since July 2001. From 1992 to July 1998, he served as the President of Clinique Laboratories, Inc. and the Senior Officer of that division since 1992. From 1988 to 1992, Mr. Brestle served as the President of Prescriptives U.S.A. He joined Prescriptives as a Vice President, National Sales Manager, doubling the business in four years. He served as a Regional Marketing Director for Aramis in 1983. In 1973, Mr. Brestle joined Johnson & Johnson, where he gained distribution, manufacturing and operations experience. He served in the United States Air Force for six years. He has been an Independent Director of DineEquity, Inc. since July 2009. He is a Director of Bite Tech, Inc. since October 2010. He serves as a Vice Chairman of The Cosmetic, Toiletry and Fragrance Association and the Contributions Chairman for the Look Good.Feel Better program. He has been the Chairman of the Board of Directors for the Personal Care Products Council since February 2008. Mr. Brestle serves on the Advisory Council of the College of Commerce and Finance for Villanova University and as an Honorary Member of the Board of Trustees of Shore Memorial Health Foundation. He was a Board Member of Airborne. He served as an Independent Director of Abercrombie & Fitch Co. from June 15, 2005 to July 13, 2007. Mr. Brestle graduated with B.S. from Villanova University in 1967.Read Full Background




